# 📊 CORD-19 Data Explorer

This project explores the **CORD-19 COVID-19 research dataset**, focusing on paper metadata.  
It includes **data cleaning, analysis, visualization**, and an **interactive Streamlit app**.

---

## 📂 Project Structure
project/
├── metadata/
│ └── metadata.csv # download from (https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/allen-institute-for-ai/CORD-19-research-challenge?select=metadata.csv)
├── cord19_analysis.ipynb # Jupyter Notebook / Python script for exploration
└── app.py # Streamlit interactive app


---

## 📝 Features

1. **Data Exploration**
   - Loads `metadata.csv`
   - Checks dimensions, column types, missing values
   - Generates basic statistics

2. **Data Cleaning**
   - Handles missing values in `title` and `publish_time`
   - Converts `publish_time` to datetime
   - Extracts publication year
   - Computes abstract word count

3. **Analysis & Visualization**
   - Number of publications by year
   - Top 10 journals publishing COVID-19 research
   - Frequent words in paper titles
   - Word cloud of paper titles

4. **Streamlit App**
   - Interactive year filter
   - Bar charts for publications and top journals
   - Word cloud visualization
   - Displays a sample of filtered data

---

## ⚙️ Installation

1. Clone or download the project.
2. Install required Python packages:
```bash
pip install pandas matplotlib streamlit wordcloud


1. Run Data Analysis Notebook/Script
python cord19_analysis.py

2. Run Streamlit App

